  keywords = {adenine nucleotide translocase, ANT, autoantibody, dilated cardiomyopathy, myocarditis, incidence, cardiac function},
  note     = {Cross-sectional study; DCM n=37, myocarditis n=12, controls/other cardiac diseases (negative). Anti-ANT prevalence: 16\% (6/37) in DCM and 42\% (5/12) in myocarditis. Antibodies negative in all control and other cardiac disease groups. No statistically significant correlation found between anti-ANT titre and cardiac parameters (LVEF, LVDd, CTR), suggesting possible compensatory mechanisms or minor pathogenic role. Contrasts with the 94\% prevalence in Schultheiss 1985 — likely reflecting methodological differences and patient selection. Limitations: cross-sectional; Japanese cohort (generalisability uncertain); methodological differences from Schultheiss cohort.},
